UID:5vacJNG0Prb85-w_0Bpwx
SUMMARY:Rice360 Global Health Technologies Seminar Series: AI Driven Wearab
	le Sensors for Maternal and Newborn Health in Low Resource Settings
DTSTAMP:20260630T135114Z
DTSTART:20260901T220000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join Rice360 for engaging conversations with leaders in global 
	health and development as they share their expert insights on the intersec
	tion of medicine\, technology and policy.  Steve Xu\, MD\, MSc is a physic
	ian-engineer\, entrepreneur\, and board-certified dermatologist. He is the
	 CEO and co-founder of Sibel Health as well as the Ruth K. Freinkel\, MD P
	rofessor at Northwestern University. He received his undergraduate degree 
	in bioengineering from Rice University summa cum laude\, an MD from Harvar
	d Medical School (Soros Fellow)\, and a Masters in Health Policy from The 
	London School of Economics (Marshall Scholar). Dr. Xu has authored more th
	an 120 peer-reviewed publications and listed as an inventor on 15 pending 
	and granted patents. As both an NIH\, Gates Foundation\, FDA\, and DoD fun
	ded investigator\, he has led complex engineering\, artificial intelligenc
	e\, and clinical development efforts worldwide. As an MIT 35 Under 35 Tech
	nology innovator\, his publications have appeared in Nature\, Science\, Th
	e Proceedings of the National Academy of Medicine\, and the New England Jo
	urnal of Medicine garnering press attention from The New York Times\, CNN\
	, The Washington Post\, and The Los Angeles Times. Within 4 years of found
	ing\, Sibel Health has obtained six FDA 510(k) clearances\, monitored more
	 than 16\,000 individuals\, and launched in more than 20 countries worldwi
	de with its ICU-grade wearable sensors for maternal neonatal health.\n\nht
	tps://events.rice.edu/event/432735-rice360-global-health-technologies-semi
	nar-series\n\nFrom Rice University - Open to the Public
URL:https://events.rice.edu/event/432735-rice360-global-health-technologies
	-seminar-series
GEO:29.7174;-95.4018
LOCATION:BioScience Research Collaborative
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:rice-public-events
CATEGORIES:Rice University - Open to the Public
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
